'''Gonçalo Matias Ramos''' ({{IPA|pt|ɡõˈsalu ˈʁɐmuʃ}}; born 20 June 2001) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|striker]] for {{French football updater|PSG}} club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

Born in [[Olhão]], Ramos came through [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s [[S.L. Benfica (youth)|youth academy]]. He began playing for [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]] in 2019 and was promoted to the first team a year later. Following three seasons with the first team, Ramos established himself as an integral player for the club, helping them win the [[Primeira Liga|league title]] in [[2022–23 Primeira Liga|2022–23]]. In 2023, Ramos signed for Paris Saint-Germain on an initial one-year loan deal, before joining the club permanently for €65 million. With PSG, he won three [[Ligue 1]] titles and two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de France]], including two [[UEFA Champions League]] titles back-to-back in [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2025]] and [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|2026]], with the former being part of a [[continental treble]]. 

Ramos is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various levels, including the [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] that finished as runners-up at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2019 UEFA European Championship]] and the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 team]] that finished as runners-up at the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2021 European Championship]]. He made his senior international debut in 2022, being part of the squad at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Olhão]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gonçalo Ramos |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/786847/contextId/176 |access-date=2 August 2022 |website=FPF |language=pt-PT}}</ref> [[Faro (Portuguese district)|Faro District]], Ramos started his football career in the youth ranks of local side [[S.C. Olhanense|Olhanense]] in 2009, before joining Loulé in 2011. Shortly Ramos had several trials with [[Sporting CP]] aged 9, but was rejected due to his slight frame, leading him to join their [[Lisbon derby|crosstown rivals]] youth system [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2013 at the age of 12.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/sporting-chumbou-goncalo-ramos|title=Sporting chumbou Gonçalo Ramos|website=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=9 December 2022|access-date=9 December 2022|archive-date=9 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221209180345/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/benfica/detalhe/sporting-chumbou-goncalo-ramos|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Benfica===
====2019–22: Rise to the first team====
On 13 January 2019, he made his professional debut with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] as an 84th-minute substitute for [[Nuno Tavares]] in a 3–2 home loss to [[S.C. Braga|Braga B]] in [[2018–19 LigaPro|LigaPro]].<ref>{{ForaDeJogo|200106200001|access-date=15 January 2019}}</ref> On 21 July 2020, he made his first-team debut with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] as an 85th-minute substitute for [[Pizzi (Portuguese footballer)|Pizzi]] in a 4–0 away win over [[C.D. Aves|Desportivo das Aves]] in the [[2019–20 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]], netting a brace in 8 minutes.{{citation needed|date=July 2025}} During that season, Ramos played in the [[2019–20 UEFA Youth League]], in which he was a key part of Benfica reaching the final of the competition, lost to [[Real Madrid CF (youth)|Real Madrid]] (3–2), in which he scored a brace in the finals; he finished as joint-top scorer in the tournament with eight goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Youth-league-benfica-en-demi-finales-grace-a-goncalo-ramos/1162437|title=Youth League:Benfica in the semi-finals thanks to Gonçalo Ramos|website=lequipe.fr|date=18 August 2020}}</ref> On 7 October 2020, he agreed to a contract extension to 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gonçalo Ramos renews contract |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2020/10/07/futebol-benfica-goncalo-ramos-contrato-renovacao-ate-2025 |access-date=16 April 2022 |website=www.slbenfica.pt}}</ref>

After a promising [[2020–21 S.L. Benfica season|2020–21]] season with the [[S.L. Benfica B|B team]], which he scored eleven goals in twelve games, Ramos was given a run in the first-team at the start of the [[2021–22 S.L. Benfica season|2021–22]] season by manager [[Jorge Jesus]], starting in a 2–0 home victory over [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]] in the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|third qualifying round]] of the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2198-joao-mario-goal-sees-benfica-through-with-comfort|title=João Mário goal sees Benfica through with comfort|publisher=PortuGOAL|last=Ribeiro|first=Patrick|date=10 August 2021|access-date=10 August 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.footballtransfers.com/en/transfer-news/pt-liga-portugal/2021-11-who-is-goncalo-ramos-benficas-gem-wanted-bayern|title=Who is Goncalo Ramos? Benfica's gem wanted by Bayern|website=footballtransfers.com|first=Martin|last=Macdonald|date=20 September 2022|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=9 August 2021 |title=Jorge Jesus elogia Gonçalo Ramos e reclama louros da sua evolução |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/jorge-jesus-elogia-goncalo-ramos-e-reclama-louros-da-sua-evolucao-14019357.html |access-date=6 December 2022 |work=Diário de Notícias |language=pt}}</ref> Following the arrival of [[Roman Yaremchuk]] and the return of [[Darwin Núñez]] from injury, Ramos found limited first-team minutes, leading him to pursue a move out of the club in the winter [[transfer window]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 January 2022 |title=Saída de Jesus travou ida de Gonçalo Ramos para clube inglês |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1910015/sada-de-jesus-travou-ida-de-gonalo-ramos-para-clube-ingls |website=Notícias ao Minuto}}</ref> With the arrival of interim manager [[Nélson Veríssimo]] in January 2022, who had previously coached him at the B team, Ramos began playing more regularly, and reignited his form, scoring seven goals and adding two assists. His versatility enabled him to play in various positions in attack, which the new coach found useful.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 March 2022 |title=Gonçalo Ramos agarra vaga no onze e vai ser aumentado |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1959551/goncalo-ramos-agarra-vaga-no-onze-e-vai-ser-aumentado |website=Notícias ao Minuto}}</ref>

On 13 April, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 3–3 away draw against [[Liverpool FC|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]] in the second leg of the [[UEFA Champions League]] [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League#Knockout phase|quarter-finals]] tie.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/amp/noticias/ver/936568|title=BENFICA DESPEDE-SE COM HONRA (E GOLOS) DIANTE DO LIVERPOOL|access-date=16 April 2022|archive-date=8 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220508134941/https://www.abola.pt/amp/noticias/ver/936568|url-status=dead}}</ref> In doing so, he became the second youngest player (aged 20 years and 297 days) to score for the club in the final phases of the competition, though Benfica were eliminated after losing to Liverpool 6–4 on aggregate.<ref name=":0"/>

====2022–23: Breakthrough season and league title====
[[File:GonçaloRamos22.jpg|thumb|upright|Ramos playing for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2022]]
Ramos began the [[2022–23 S.L. Benfica season|2022–23]] season by scoring his first career [[hat-trick]] on 2 August in a 4–1 home win over [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in the first leg of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round|2022–23 UEFA Champions League third qualifying round]].<ref>{{cite web |date=2 August 2022 |title=Hat-trick de Gonçalo Ramos na goleada do Benfica |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/jogos-em-direto-15064750.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221001043322/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/jogos-em-direto-15064750.html |archive-date=1 October 2022 |access-date=11 August 2022 |publisher=[[Diário de Notícias]]}}</ref> His prolific form saw him score two more goals and provided two assists, as part of a partnership with newly signed teammate [[David Neres]], including a goal and an assist in the 3–0 home win over [[Dynamo Kiev]] in the second leg of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round|2022–23 UEFA Champions League play-off round]], helping his side qualify to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |date=23 September 2022 |title=Ao intervalo Benfica - Dínamo Kiev: veja o 'filme' dos primeiros 45 minutos |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/liga-dos-campeoes/artigos/ao-intervalo-benfica-x-dinamo-kiev-veja-o-filme-dos-primeiros-45-minutos |publisher=Sapo Desporto}}</ref> On 2 November, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal of the season, opening Benfica's 6–1 away win against [[Maccabi Haifa FC|Maccabi Haifa]] in their last [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|2022–23 UEFA Champions League group stage]] match, to ensure the club's qualification to the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of sixteen]], as group winners.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2894-benfica-crush-maccabi-haifa-to-snatch-top-spot-from-psg-in-group-h|title=Benfica crush Maccabi Haifa to snatch top spot from PSG in Group H|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Marshall|last=Matthew|date=2 November 2022|access-date=2 November 2022}}</ref> After scoring five goals in five matches, he was named the league's Player of the Month and Forward of the Month for the months of October and November.<ref name="FWAward">{{cite web |date=15 December 2022 |title=Melhores de outubro/novembro: Gonçalo Ramos é o Avançado do Mês na Liga Portugal bwin |url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20222023/noticias/geral/premios-mensais/outubronovembro/melhores-de-outubronovembro-goncalo-ramos-e-o-avancado-do-mes-na-liga-portugal-bwin/ |publisher=[[Primeira Liga|Liga Portugal]]}}</ref>

On 15 January 2023, Ramos scored a brace to help the hosts secure a 2–2 draw against crosstown rivals [[Sporting CP]] in the [[Lisbon derby]], being named man of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/3018-sporting-hold-benfica-to-2-2-draw-in-entertaining-lisbon-derby|title=Sporting hold Benfica to 2-2 draw in entertaining Lisbon derby|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=1 February 2021|access-date=15 January 2023}}</ref> In doing so, he became the second youngest player (aged 21 years and 183 days) to score a brace in the derby, since [[António Mendes (footballer)|António Mendes]] (aged 21 years and 30 days) in 1958.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ribeiro |first=Patrick |date=15 January 2023 |title=Desde 1958 que ninguém tão jovem bisava no dérbi da 2ª Circular |url=https://www.zerozero.pt/news.php?id=434037 |access-date=15 January 2023 |publisher=ZeroZero}}</ref> On 7 March, in the second leg of [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League#Round of 16|Champions League round-of-16]], Ramos scored a brace in a 5–1 home win against [[Club Brugge]], becoming the youngest Portuguese player (aged 21 years and 260 days) to score twice in a Champions League knockout stage match.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 March 2023 |title=Gonçalo Ramos faz história na Liga dos Campeões |url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2023-03-07/benfica-goncalo-ramos-faz-historia-na-liga-dos-campeoes/979251 |access-date=8 March 2023 |publisher=[[A Bola]]}}</ref> On 2 April, he scored the only goal of an away win over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]], making the youngest player to score 25 goals in a season for Benfica, since [[Eusébio]] in the 1962–1963 season.<ref>{{cite web |date=2 April 2023 |title=Desde Eusébio que ninguém tão jovem marcava 25 golos |url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2023-04-03/desde-eusebio-que-ninguem-tao-jovem-marcava-25-golos/982435 |access-date=2 April 2023 |publisher=[[A Bola]] |archive-date=10 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230410052334/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2023-04-03/desde-eusebio-que-ninguem-tao-jovem-marcava-25-golos/982435 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Ramos finished the season with 27 goals for his team, including one on the final day of the league campaign, in a 3–0 win over [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] to seal the title for Benfica, their first title in four years; his 19 league goals put him second for the season.<ref name="PLiga">{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/3242-benfica-crowned-champions-of-portugal|title=Benfica crowned champions of Portugal|publisher=PortuGOAL|last=Kundert|first=Tom|date=27 May 2023|access-date=27 May 2023}}</ref>

=== Paris Saint-Germain ===
[[File:Ramos asse psg 2425.png|thumb|upright|Ramos with [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2025]]

====2023–24: Debut season and domestic treble====
On 7 August 2023, [[Ligue 1]] side [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] announced the signing of Ramos on a season-long loan,<ref>{{cite web|date=7 August 2023|title=Gonçalo Ramos is a Parisian!|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/goncalo-ramos-is-a-parisian-mercato-2324-first-team|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.}}</ref> having an option-to-buy at the end of the season for a reported fee of €65 million, with an additional €15 million in potential bonuses.<ref>{{Cite news |date=7 August 2023 |title=Paris St-Germain sign Ramos on loan from Benfica |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66434185 |access-date=8 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Crafton |first1=Adam |date=6 August 2023 |title=PSG agree deal to sign Benfica striker Goncalo Ramos |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4753675/2023/08/06/goncalo-ramos-psg-benfica-transfer/ |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=[[The Athletic]] |language=en}}</ref> Sources claimed that the buy option was mandatory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 August 2023 |title=Goncalo Ramos: Paris Saint-Germain complete signing of Portugal international striker from Benfica |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/transfers/2023-2024/goncalo-ramos-paris-saint-germain-complete-signing-of-portugal-international-striker-from-benfica_sto9734606/story.shtml |access-date=8 August 2023 |website=Eurosport |language=en}}</ref>

Ramos made his debut in a 0–0 draw against [[FC Lorient|Lorient]] at the [[Parc des Princes]] on 12 August.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 August 2023 |title=Paris Saint-Germain V Lorient |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202324/paris-saint-germain-v-lorient |access-date=12 August 2023 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.}}</ref> On 24 September, Ramos scored his first two goals for PSG in his sixth appearance in a 4–0 win over [[Le Classique]] rivals [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]], after replacing [[Kylian Mbappé]] in the 32nd minute. He also became the first player in Ligue 1 after his teammate Mbappé to score a brace coming off the bench in October 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 September 2023 |title=Kolo Muani and Ramos score maiden PSG goals in win over Marseille |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/kolo-muani-ramos-score-maiden-psg-goals-win-over-marseille-2023-09-24/ |access-date=25 September 2023 |publisher=Reuters}}</ref> On 22 November, PSG announced that it had exercised its buy option in Ramos's loan deal. He signed a contract with the club until 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 November 2023 |title=Le Paris Saint-Germain lève l'option d'achat de Gonçalo Ramos |trans-title=Paris Saint-Germain exercises Gonçalo Ramos's buy option |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/le-paris-saint-germain-leve-loption-dachat-de-goncalo-ramos |access-date=22 November 2023 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]] |language=Fr}}</ref> On 24 November, Ramos scored his first goal since signing permanently with the club in a 5–2 win at home over [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-24 |title=PSG feasts thanks to the rhythm of Dembélé and Mbappe |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/ligue-1/2023/11/24/65610f8746163fb37f8b45d5.html |access-date=2023-11-24 |website=MARCA |language=en}}</ref>

Shortly after, he caught a virus, which caused him to lose six kilograms, with the situation getting worse in December, leading Ramos to be hospitalised, with PSG requesting Benfica's help in the entire logistics and monitoring his process, which they accepted. The situation was confirmed by PSG's manager [[Luis Enrique]] on 19 January 2024, and after recovering, his form improved in the new year, scoring five goals in seven matches including, on 31 March, closing the 2–0 win over Marseille in the Le Classique at ''[[Stade Vélodrome]]'', after replacing Kylian Mbappé in the 65th minute.<ref>{{cite web |date=15 January 2024 |title=Virose atacou Gonçalo Ramos e obrigou a internamento no hospital |url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/paises/franca/psg/detalhe/virose-atacou-goncalo-ramos-e-obrigou-a-internamento-no-hospital}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=19 January 2024 |title=Luis Enrique confirma doença de Gonçalo Ramos e deixa garantia|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/luis-enrique-confirma-doenca-de-goncalo-ramos-e-deixa-garantia-2024011914193614461}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=31 March 2024 |title=Vitinha e Gonçalo Ramos marcaram os golos da vitória do PSG em Marselha|url=https://www.dnoticias.pt/2024/3/31/399926-vitinha-e-goncalo-ramos-marcaram-os-golos-da-vitoria-do-psg-em-marselha/}}</ref> The rest of the season, Ramos served more as a back-up due to his condition, he would score 14 goals in his [[2023–24 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|first season]], while helping his team win the [[Treble (association football)|domestic treble]] with record-extending successes in [[Ligue 1]], the [[Coupe de France]], and the [[Trophée des Champions]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/coupe-de-france/psg-enrique-a-la-recherche-de-joueurs-qui-veulent-venir-marquer-l-histoire-du-club-20240526|title="La Ligue des champions, on la gagnera": Luis Enrique confiant et (très) ambitieux pour l'après-Mbappé au PSG|trans-title="The Champions League, we will win it": Luis Enrique confident and (very) ambitious for PSG's post-Mbappé|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|last=Remise|first=Christophe|language=fr|date=25 May 2024|access-date=26 May 2024|archive-date=25 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240525225608/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/coupe-de-france/psg-enrique-a-la-recherche-de-joueurs-qui-veulent-venir-marquer-l-histoire-du-club-20240526|url-status=live}}</ref> while also reaching the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League semi-finals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68965987|title=Paris St-Germain 0–1 Borussia Dortmund (0–2 agg): Germans move into Champions League final at Wembley|publisher=BBC Sport|last=Emons|first=Michael|date=7 May 2024|access-date=26 May 2024|archive-date=26 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240526022350/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68965987|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2024–present: Consecutive league titles and European champion====
On 16 August, in PSG's opening match of the [[2024–25 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|new season]] against [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]], after Ramos assisted his side opening goal, he was forced off after sustaining an injury following a challenge from [[Étienne Youte Kinkoue]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2024-08-16 |title=PSG opens post-Mbappé era with 4-1 win at Le Havre in French league |url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/soccer/french-league-results-psg-s29370 |access-date=2024-08-16 |website=Newsday |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=João Neves makes debut |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/joao-neves-makes-debut-le-havre-ac-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-20242025 |access-date=17 August 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=Gonçalo Ramos suffers 'serious injury' in PSG's season opener against Le Havre|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/goncalo-ramos-suffers-serious-injury-in-psgs-season-opener-against-le-havre/ |access-date=17 August 2024 |publisher=Get French Football News}}</ref> After three months, he made his return from injury, on 26 November, replacing [[Bradley Barcola]] in the 72nd minute of a 1–0 loss to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/nation/2024/11/600_387144.html |title=Kim Min-jae scores for Bayern in Champions League win over Lee Kang-in's PSG |publisher=Korea Times |date=27 November 2024}}</ref> On 10 December, Ramos scored his first Champions League goal for PSG in a 3–0 away win against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 December 2024 |title=Gonçalo Ramos mata, Nuno Mendes esfola e o PSG ganha: franceses vencem RB Salzburgo e entram na zona do playoff |url=https://observador.pt/2024/12/10/goncalo-ramos-mata-nuno-mendes-esfola-e-o-psg-ganha-franceses-vencem-rb-salzburgo-e-entram-na-zona-do-playoff/}}</ref>

On 19 February 2025, in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Knockout phase play-offs|Champions League knockout phase play-offs]], he got on the scoresheet in a 7–0 win over fellow Ligue 1 side [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], scoring PSG sixth goal, and helping his side secure a 10–0 aggregate victory to advance to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG 7–0 Brest: French champions stroll into last 16 with 10–0 aggregate win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c98y71v52ngt |publisher=BBC |work=BBC Sport |date=19 February 2025 |access-date=19 February 2025}}</ref> On 26 February, he scored his first hat-trick for the club, netting three goals in a 7–0 win over [[Stade Briochin]] in the quarter-finals of the [[Coupe de France]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=26 February 2025 |title=João Neves abriu caminho ao show de Gonçalo Ramos na goleada do PSG |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/joao-neves-abriu-caminho-ao-show-de-goncalo-ramos-na-goleada-do-psg-2025022622080264707 |access-date=27 February 2025 |work=A Bola }}</ref> Having helped PSG secure their 13th Ligue 1 title, Ramos scored his first Ligue 1 hat-trick on 10 May, netting three goals in a 4–1 away win over [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c7vn674q55lt |title=PSG 1–0 Angers SCO |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 April 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/ligue-1-goncalo-ramos-faz-hat-trick-pelo-psg-paulo-fonseca-derrotado-2025051021115596965 |title=Ligue 1: Gonçalo Ramos faz hat trick pelo PSG, Paulo Fonseca derrotado |publisher=A Bola |date=10 May 2025 |language=pt}}</ref> At the end of the season, PSG secured their first ever Champions League title and completed a [[Treble (association football)|continental treble]].<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |title=Ousmane Dembélé élu meilleur joueur de Ligue 1 pour la première fois aux Trophées UNFP |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ousmane-dembele-elu-meilleur-joueur-de-ligue-1-pour-la-premiere-fois-aux-trophees-unfp/1561044 |access-date=2025-05-11 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0299-1de41a81a0d8-2cfefc69a802-1000--desire-doue-named-official-2025-uefa-champions-league-final/ |title=Désiré Doué named official 2025 UEFA Champions League final Player of the Match |publisher=UEFA |date=31 May 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-01 |title='I have no words' - Champions League final MVP Desire Doue pays tribute to head coach Luis Enrique for trusting PSG star to step into Kylian Mbappe's shoes {{!}} Goal.com English Saudi Arabia |url=https://www.goal.com/en-sa/lists/i-have-no-words-champions-league-final-mvp-desire-doue-pays-tribute-to-head-coach-luis-enrique-for-trusting-psg-star-to-step-into-kylian-mbappe-s-shoes/blta19ecb4df34588aa |access-date=2025-06-01 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-SA}}</ref>

In the [[2025 UEFA Super Cup]] on 13 August, Ramos was put into the field in the 77th minute when [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] held a 2–1 lead. He scored PSG's second goal in stoppage time, tying the game 2–2, which eventually PSG won 4–3 in a penalty shoot-out, with Ramos scoring PSG's first penalty.<ref>{{cite web |title=Paris vs Tottenham |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/match/2045107--paris-vs-tottenham/timeline/ |publisher=UEFA |date=13 August 2025 |access-date=14 August 2025}}</ref> On 1 October 2025, Ramos scored the winning goal against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in a 2–1 Champions League victory.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcelona 1-2 Paris St-Germain: Goncalo Ramos hits late winner in Champions League |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c1edv126d27t |access-date=2025-11-10 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> This made him the club's all-time top scorer as a substitute, with 17 goals off the bench.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-10 |title=Super-sub Ramos makes PSG history with record goal tally |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/super-sub-ramos-makes-psg-history-with-record-goal-tally-41751696 |access-date=2025-11-10 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> On 1 November, in his 100th match for PSG, he scored a stoppage-time header in a 1–0 win over [[OGC Nice|Nice]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=ENTWISTLE |first=L. |date=2025-11-03 |title=Cometh the hour, cometh the man: Goncalo Ramos, PSG's super-sub |url=https://ligue1.com/en/articles/l1_article_3564-cometh-the-hour-cometh-the-man-goncalo-ramos-psg-s-super-sub |access-date=2025-11-10 |website=Ligue 1 |language=en}}</ref> During the season, he remained a back-up for PSG as they secured their 12th league title in 14 years,<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG's Dembele named UNFP Ligue 1 Player of the Year again |url=https://www.thescore.com/fra_fed/news/3539245 |access-date=2026-05-12 |website=thescore.com |language=en}}</ref> and on 30 May, they won their second consecutive UEFA Champions League title against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]] in a penalty shootout, scoring the first penalty in the shootout to retain the trophy.<ref>{{cite web |last=Howell |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6ppx48pk2t |title=Paris Saint-Germain 1–1 Arsenal (4–3 on pens) |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
===2017–2022: Youth level and early senior career===
With the [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal under-17s]], Ramos participated in the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] in England. In this competition, he played two matches, scoring a goal against [[Slovenia national under-17 football team|Slovenia]] in a group stage exit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2024299--slovenia-vs-portugal/|title=Slovenia-Portugal &#124; Under-17 2018|website=[[UEFA]]}}</ref> Ramos was part of the [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]] team that finished runners-up to [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain]] at the [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Armenia. He was the top scorer with four goals in five appearances, including a [[hat-trick]] in a 4–0 win against the [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|Republic of Ireland]] in the semi-finals.<ref name="uefa">{{cite news|date=27 July 2019|title= Spain win 2019 U19 EURO: at a glance|url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/news/0257-0dee769d9719-c61a7e965fcc-1000--spain-win-2019-u19-euro-at-a-glance/|work=UEFA|access-date=27 July 2019}}</ref> On 12 November 2020, Ramos won his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 side]], scoring the third goal on his debut in a 3–0 victory in [[Belarus national under-21 football team|Belarus]] for the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|2021 European Championship qualification campaign]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2020/11/12/futebol-benfica-goncalo-ramos-marca-na-estreia-sub-21-portugal|title=Sub-21: Gonçalo Ramos em estreia com golo!|website=www.slbenfica.pt}}</ref> In March 2021, Ramos took part in the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], helping Portugal finish as runners-up, after losing in the final 1–0 to [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 June 2021|title=Highlights, report: Germany beat Portugal for third U21 EURO title|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/026a-127532d17acc-e079bf3c8a1c-1000--highlights-report-germany-beat-portugal-for-third-u21-euro-/|access-date=7 June 2021|website=[[UEFA]]|language=en}}</ref> On 20 September 2022, Ramos was called up to [[Portugal national football team|the senior team]] for the first time, as a replacement for Benfica team-mate [[Rafa Silva]], who retired from international football, for the upcoming [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]] matches against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gonçalo Ramos convocado por Fernando Santos |trans-title=Gonçalo Ramos called up by Fernando Santos |url=https://www.abola.pt/Nnh/Noticias/Ver/957442 |access-date=20 September 2022 |publisher=[[A Bola]] |date=20 September 2022 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920174241/https://www.abola.pt/Nnh/Noticias/Ver/957442 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===2022–present: World Cup breakthrough and Nations League title===
On 10 November 2022, Ramos was named in Portugal's 26-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite news|title=A lista de pré-convocados da Seleção para o Mundial'2022: conheça todos os nomes|trans-title=The list of pre-selected squad for the 2022 World Cup: know all the names|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/cmtv-revela-lista-de-pre-convocados-para-o-mundial2022-conheca-todos-os-nomes|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|access-date=31 October 2022|date=23 October 2022|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=10 November 2022 |title=Convocados para o Mundial 2022 |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/37061 |access-date=17 November 2022 |website=Portuguese Football Federation |language=pt}}</ref> He made his senior debut in a friendly match against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] on 17 November, scoring the third goal and assisting the fourth in a 4–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Algarvio Gonçalo Ramos estreia-se na seleção com golo e assistência... de calcanhar|trans-title=Algarvio Gonçalo Ramos makes his debut for the national team with a goal and an assist...|url=https://www.sulinformacao.pt/2022/11/algarvio-goncalo-ramos-estreia-se-na-selecao-com-golo-e-assistencia-de-calcanhar/|website=Sul Informação|date=17 November 2022|access-date=29 July 2024|language=pt}}</ref> On 6 December, Portugal manager [[Fernando Santos (footballer, born 1954)|Fernando Santos]] started Ramos ahead of [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] in the team's round of 16 game against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]]. Ramos scored a hat-trick and provided an assist in Portugal's 6–1 victory,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brown |first=James Horncastle and Luke |title=Who is Goncalo Ramos — the man who replaced Cristiano Ronaldo |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3976061/2022/12/06/goncalo-ramos-cristiano-ronaldo-portugal/|website=[[The Athletic]]|date=6 December 2022 |access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> becoming the first player to score a World Cup [[List of FIFA World Cup hat-tricks|knockout stage hat-trick]] since [[Tomáš Skuhravý]] in [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/portugal-switzerland-result-final-score-b2239867.html|title=Who needs Ronaldo? Ramos hat-trick powers Portugal into World Cup quarter-finals|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=7 December 2022t}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285073/400128130|title=Portugal 6–1 Switzerland|website=FIFA|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> He also became the first player to score a hat-trick in his first World Cup start since [[Miroslav Klose]] in [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]].<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/world-cup-2022/2022/1206/1340277-portugals-ramos-dazzles-with-hat-trick-against-swiss/|title=Portugal's Ramos dazzles with hat-trick against Swiss|website=[[RTÉ]]|date=6 December 2022}}</ref> Portugal employed the same strategy in the quarter-finals against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], with Ramos starting once again, but Portugal lost 1–0, being eliminated from the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Glendenning |first=Barry |date=10 December 2022 |title=Morocco 1-0 Portugal: World Cup 2022 quarter-final – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/10/morocco-portugal-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live |access-date=11 November 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ronaldo equals men's international appearance record |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/ronaldo-equals-mens-international-appearance-record|website=[[FIFA]]|access-date=17 December 2022}}</ref>

Following the World Cup, with the arrival of new manager [[Roberto Martínez]], Ramos lost his place to Ronaldo in Portugal's squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|qualifiers]] against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] and [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Roberto Martinez names Cristiano Ronaldo in first Portugal squad since World Cup|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/portugal-por/story/4902954/ronaldo-named-in-roberto-martinez-first-portugal-squad|website=[[ESPN]]|date=17 March 2023|access-date=24 March 2023}}</ref> After Ronaldo was suspended in a qualifier match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]], Ramos was given a chance to score brace in Portugal's 9–0 home defeat of Luxembourg on 11 September, Portugal's biggest win in international history.<ref>{{cite web|first=Pedro|last=Lemos|title=Portugal 9–0 Luxemburgo (crónica)|trans-title=Portugal 9–0 Luxembourg (report)|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/portugal/selecao-nacional/portugal-9-0-luxemburgo-cronica|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|date=11 September 2023|access-date=11 September 2023}}</ref> On 13 October, Ramos scored the opening goal in a 3–2 win over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]], leading Portugal to qualify for [[Euro 2024]], marking the nation's fastest qualification to a major tournament in their history.<ref>{{cite news|title=Portugal já está no Euro-2024 (e com a qualificação mais rápida de sempre!)|url=https://www.abola.pt/selecao/noticias/portugal-ja-esta-no-euro-2024-e-com-a-qualificacao-mais-rapida-de-sempre-2023101320423428087|website=[[A Bola]]|access-date=13 October 2023|language=pt}}</ref>

On 21 May 2024, he was named in Portugal's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024|final tournament]] in Germany,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx88ljwp5x8o|title=Ronaldo named in Portugal squad for Euro 2024|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=21 May 2024|access-date=3 July 2024}}</ref> where Portugal was eliminated from the tournament by [[France national football team|France]] in the quarter-finals, after losing 5–3 in a [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Emma|last=Sanders|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024 }}</ref>

In May 2025, Ramos was selected for Portugal’s [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Portugal|squad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada |trans-title=Nations League squad announced |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645 |website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |language=pt |access-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> He and his team would go on to win the tournament [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|5–3 in a penalty shootout]] over rivals [[Spain national football team|Spain]], with Ramos scoring Portugal's first penalty.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/|title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first1=Tim|last1=Spiers|first2=Dermot|last2=Corrigan|first3=Stu|last3=James|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Ramos is capable of playing in several offensive positions, such as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]], or [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]]. He usually drops deep to help his team build their attacking play by bringing his teammates into play and creating chances for other players. Due to his awareness and willingness to follow instructions, he understands how to rotate positions in ways in which to benefit the ball-holder with his movement, short or long passes. When he is offering short, he aims to be positive in his control of the ball, he attempts to open his body up each time, with either foot, being able to hold up the ball and act as his team focal point in attack.<ref name=":Style of play1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.scoutedftbl.com/best-young-football-players/goncalo-ramos/|title=Profiling Benfica's Gonçalo Ramos|work=Scouted Football|access-date=19 October 2022|archive-date=19 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221019003637/https://www.scoutedftbl.com/best-young-football-players/goncalo-ramos/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=":Style of play2">{{Cite web|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/goncalo-ramos-at-benfica-2022-23-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics|title = Gonçalo Ramos: The latest on the conveyor belt of talent|website=totalfootballanalysis.com|first=Christopher|last=Winter| date=30 August 2022 |access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref>

During his second season at Benfica, under [[Roger Schmidt (footballer)|Roger Schmidt]], Ramos was used as a striker in a [[4–2–3–1]] formation. His ability to attack space and create further space both inside and outside the penalty area with his movement is what made the move to the centre a more natural progression. Ramos is good at picking up positions between the opposition's defenders and then exploiting space behind the defensive line. He presses with intent and is not afraid to put himself about against the opposition. Ramos usually links up with the midfield and makes proactive movements which always can put a striker in a goal-scoring position more often rather than standing around and waiting for the service, similar to [[Karim Benzema]].<ref name=":Style of play1"/><ref name=":Style of play2"/>

==Personal life==
Ramos' father, Manuel Ramos, originally from [[Amareleja]], [[Beja District]], is also a former Portugal youth international who represented [[S.C. Farense|Farense]] among other Portuguese clubs.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=8 December 2022 |title=Luís Osório revela história do pai de Gonçalo Ramos: "Foi esse o segredo que […] guardaram até ontem…" |url=https://www.hiper.fm/luis-osorio-revela-historia-do-pai-de-goncalo-ramos-foi-esse-o-segredo-que-o-goncalo-e-o-seu-pai-guardaram-ate-ontem/ |access-date=10 December 2022 |website=Hiper Fm {{!}} Agarra a tua música! |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

